    "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nWhenever I am in a group chat with people I don't have in my contacts, adn they send a message, it shows it as ```31612345678 ~John```. I want to retrieve their nickname, ```John``` in this example, so I can send them \"personal\" messages. Attached image shows what I mean.\r\n![nickname](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/1252824/1915101/eb625c1e-7d61-11e3-9935-95995d4d38e2.png)\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "body": "In a group message the number of the author is just [author].\r\nin a group message the name of the author is the same as normal: [name] it's in the notify tag.\r\n\r\n\r\nHow I got the $: [It is possible with event but for me this was sufficient]\r\n```\r\n$msgs=$wa->getMessages(); //store all messages in $msgs\r\nforeach($msgs as $m){\r\n      $attri = $m->getAttributes();\r\n      $author = $attri[author];\r\n       foreach (($m->getChildren()) as $child) {\r\n\t           if (($child->getTag()) == \"body\") {\r\n\t\t           $body = $child->getData();\r\n\t           }\r\n\t           else if (($child->getTag()) == \"notify\") {\r\n\t\t           $name = $child->getAttribute('name');\r\n\t           }\r\n}\r\n```",
