            "body": "In a group message the number of the author is [author].\r\nin a group message the name of the author is the same as normal: [name]\r\n\r\nIn a personal message the number is: [from]\r\nIn a personal message the name is: [name]\r\n\r\nIf you want to use the number/groupnumber I suggest you cut of the last part beginning with the @. Use Code below to do that:\r\n``` php\r\n$from = str_replace(\"@s.whatsapp.net\", \"\", $from); //remove @.swhatsapp.net\r\n$from = str_replace(\"@g.us\",\"\",$from); //remove @g.us\r\n``` \r\n",
